Example with increased
limit
contaning partial results
Requesting a high number of results (e.g., limit: 100) can affect the response format. Specifically it often includes only location_id and location_type.

Setting a larger limit increases the likelihood of receiving partial data (e.g., only location_id) instead of full details. A smaller limit (e.g., 30) is more likely to return complete details for the locations.

